2138void
2139JPTextEncoder::EncodeShiftJIS(const std::wstring& str, std::string& bytes)
2140{
2141 static const char replacement = '?';
2142 //int invalid = 0;
2143 bytes.resize(2 * str.length() + 1);
2144 int index = 0;
2145 for (wchar_t ch : str) {
2146 unsigned j;
2147 if (ch < 0x80) {
2148 // ASCII
2149 bytes[index++] = static_cast<uint8_t>(ch);
2150 } else if ((j = unicodeToJisx0201(Hi(ch), Lo(ch))) != 0) {
2151 // JIS X 0201 Latin or JIS X 0201 Kana
2152 bytes[index++] = static_cast<uint8_t>(j);
2153 } else if ((j = unicodeToSjis(Hi(ch), Lo(ch))) != 0) {
2154 // JIS X 0208
2155 bytes[index++] = static_cast<uint8_t>(j >> 8);
2156 bytes[index++] = static_cast<uint8_t>(j & 0xff);
2157 } else if ((j = unicodeToJisx0212(Hi(ch), Lo(ch))) != 0) {
2158 // JIS X 0212 (can't be encoded in ShiftJIS !)
2159 bytes[index++] = static_cast<uint8_t>(0x81); // white square
2160 bytes[index++] = static_cast<uint8_t>(0xa0); // white square
2161 } else {
2162 // Error
2163 bytes[index++] = replacement;
2164 //++invalid;
2165 }
2166 }
2167 bytes.resize(index);
